entry.summary:
White marble base capital 0.63 × 0.29 × 0.715. inscribed on one face;
            the inscription must have continued on the base below. Date: Second century A.D.
            (lettering). Photo. Excavated by the NYU expedition in 1969 (69.363). Unpublished.

White marble block (0.85 x 0.58 x 0.55). Inscribed on the face. Date:
            First to fourth centuries A.D. (lettering). Photo. Recorded by the NYU expedition (DM;
            Walls 153). Unpublished.

Sarcophagus lid. 'On the lid'. Date: First to fourth centuries A.D.
            (context). Copied by Fellows; not reported subsequently. Published by Fellows, no. 69;
            by Boeckh, from Fellows, CIG 2850g, p.1119 whence McCabe PHI Aphrodisias 560 .
